cs.AR, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.DL

The paper discusses a unified architecture for next generation cognitive, low cost, mobile internet that takes computing out of the data center and into the end user platform. This suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (AI), neural networks (NE), and distributed computing (DC). The paper also mentions machine learning, natural language processing (NLP), and deep learning (DL), which further supports the likelihood of cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.DL as potential sub-categories. Finally, the use of the Java virtual machine (JVM) suggests a potential connection to computer architecture (cs.AR).
